The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Sunday, March 28, 2004 				 Carlos the Jackal lawyer to defend Saddam 
				 	 Jacques Verges																								Paris, March 27 (Reuters): The French lawyer known for defending Nazi war criminal Klaus Barbie and guerrilla Carlos the Jackal said today that Saddam Husseins nephew had chosen him to represent the deposed Iraqi President.																								Jacques Verges, who is also defending former Iraqi deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz, confirmed the details of a French newspaper report that he would lead Saddams defence.																								The Iraqi governing council in Baghdad is setting up a war crimes tribunal to try Saddam on charges which may include genocide and crimes against humanity. 																								French daily Le Parisien said Verges had outlined a possible defence strategy based on US support for Saddam in the 1980s and believed US defence secretary Donald Rumsfeld might have to testify in any trial. 
